1009: Pathogen: clinical or host-associated sample from Escherichia coli
Identifiers: BioSample: SAMN15181529; Sample name: BL-II-11(3)
Organism: Escherichia coli
Attributes:
    /strain="BL-II-11(3)"
    /collected by="Michele Cadena, Marco Aurelio Vianello"
    /collection date="2013-03-01"
    /geographic location="Brazil: Amazonas"
    /host="Homo sapiens"
    /host disease="not applicable"
    /isolation source="feces"
    /latitude and longitude="0.111145 S 67.097841 W"
Description:
Escherichia coli is a priority pathogen that infects humans and animals, been widely associated with hospital-acquired infections in immunocompromised patients. In this respect, the whole-genome sequencing of multidrug-resistant Escherichia coli ST393 isolated from indigenous communities in the Brazilian Amazon has given insights to better understand such clinically significant pathogen.
Accession: SAMN15181529	ID: 15181529
